  "bio": [
    "Gordon Wu is the chairman of Hopewell Holdings, one of the largest commercial landlords in Hong Kong's Wan Chai business district.",
    "The Princeton University-educated tycoon also boasts interests in power and transportation infrastructure projects in mainland China.",
    "Son Thomas Jefferson was deputy chairman and managing director of Hopewell until 2019. He sits on the board of Asian casino giant Melco Resorts & Entertainment.",
    "In 2019, Wu took Hopewell private from the Hong Kong stock exchange in a HK$21 billion ($2.7 billion) deal."
  ],
  "about": [
    "The Queen of England conferred upon Wu the title of Knight Commander of the Order of St. Michael and St. George in 1997 for his contribution to Asian infrastructure."
  ]
